# nws-ez

A tiny, practical wrapper around https://api.weather.gov (NWS weather.gov API).

## Why
Because the official API is fine, but doing the multi-step “points → grid → forecast/stations” dance every time is annoying.

## Quickstart

```py
from nws_ez import NWSClient

client = NWSClient(user_agent="my-app/1.0 (me@example.com)")

# Forecast
fc = client.forecast(38.8977, -77.0365)  # White House coords
print(fc.periods[0].name, fc.periods[0].temperature, fc.periods[0].short_forecast)

# Hourly
hourly = client.hourly(38.8977, -77.0365)
print(hourly.periods[0].start_time, hourly.periods[0].temperature)

# Latest observation near that point
obs = client.latest_observation(38.8977, -77.0365)
print(obs.timestamp, obs.temperature_c, obs.wind_speed_mps)

# Active alerts for a point
alerts = client.alerts_active(point=(38.8977, -77.0365))
print(len(alerts.features), "active alerts")
